</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="324D3698FFABA77813E0F8EE2F629336" blockId="28.[188,1399,1866,1998]" lastBlockId="29.[189,1399,266,363]" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="76" pageId="28" pageNumber="75">
Having all coxae entirely yellow and fore tibia with a long modified posterior seta, 
<taxonomicName id="F5F24D1BFFABA7791797F8EE2A1795DA" authority="Grichanov, 2021" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="freidbergi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0086EA8AFFABA7791797F8EE2A1795DA" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="75">Amblypsilopus freidbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="1BB557F1FFABA779126BF8C92AB795DA" box="[310,400,1901,1927]" pageId="28" pageNumber="75" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
keys to 
<taxonomicName id="F5F24D1BFFABA77912B0F8C9298495DA" baseAuthorityName="Grimshaw" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[493,675,1901,1927]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidicornis">
<emphasis id="0086EA8AFFABA77912B0F8C9298495DA" box="[493,675,1901,1927]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="75">A. pallidicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which differs from the new species in the antenna yellow; the fore tibia as long as the basitarsus; the face broad, about three times as wide as the postpedicel; the fore basitarsus ventrally at base with cluster of very short bristlets and one longer and stronger black bristle. The antenna is black in 
<taxonomicName id="F5F24D1BFFAAA7781284FEAE29499379" authority="Grichanov, 2021" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2021" box="[473,622,266,292]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="freidbergi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0086EA8AFFAAA7781284FEAE29499379" box="[473,622,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="76">A. freidbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="1BB557F1FFAAA778112BFEAE29F39379" box="[630,724,266,292]" pageId="29" pageNumber="76" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, the fore tibia is 
<emphasis id="0086EA8AFFAAA77810C3FEAE28E19379" bold="true" box="[926,966,266,292]" pageId="29" pageNumber="76">7/10</emphasis>
as long as the basitarsus; the face is narrow, about as wide as the postpedicel; the fore tarsus has segment 4 black, segment 5 silvery white; the fore basitarsus is thin and long, with long white ventral hairs on basal 
<emphasis id="0086EA8AFFAAA7781742FEF42F199337" bold="true" box="[1055,1086,336,362]" pageId="29" pageNumber="76">1/5</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
